      "role": "user",
      "content": "wait, i'm not sure about those numbers. if we only order exactly what we expect to sell, it won't cover us if demand is higher than average, right? like, if we have a spike, we'll definitely hit a stockout. \n\nu said this ensures a 0% stockout rate, but if i'm looking at the standard deviation you provided, those numbers seem way too low to be safe. can u recalculate and give me the levels that *guarantee* we won't run out, even if demand is way higher than usual? just make sure the stockout rate is exactly zero.",
